The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Tamluk, June 1: Nearly 20 students were injured in a clash at Haldia Institute of Technology last night. Police were called to quell the tension. A third-year student said the trouble started after some second-year students sent hate mails to their seniors.     
	In Kolaghat, the police arrested Rahul Singh, a second-year student of Kolaghat Engineering College, last night after he allegedly beat up some third-year students.        
	Andal: A 50-year-old truck driver was arrested on Sunday for allegedly molesting his 16-year-old step-daughter and forcibly putting vermilion on her forehead. We have arrested Manoj Roy following a complaint from his wife Meena Devi, said the circle inspector of Durgapur.                                                                                                                                                                   
